summary: Providing administrative support to MIT's Laboratory for Computational Physiology (LCP) as well as assisting in production of PhysioNet, an online medical database maintained by LCP with over 60,000 registered users
Contribute to web development for PhysioNet and Critical Data websites. Help provide UX design improvements
Process and credential applicants applying to utilize our privacy-protected datasets
File and complete travel reimbursements, manage lab spreadsheets, and purchasing/ordering supples.
Budgeting food costs and general kitchen expenses for back of house operations
Providing administrative support to the kitchen manager via Microsoft Office to create schedule sheets, menu changes, and manage delivery invoices
Maintained office supplies, equipment upkeep, and storage leasing as well as purchasing new supples and equipment as needed
Managed staff schedules for both front and back of house, set up employee meetings and took notes on employee questions and concerns as needed
